<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="80" type="distribution and ecology">
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="80">Distribution and ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="80">Austral Islands (French Polynesia), only known from the type locality on slopes near the summit of Mount Pokumaru on Rapa; 550-580 m.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="80">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Appelhans, W. L. Wagner &amp; K. R. Wood" authorityYear="2014" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rutaceae" genus="Melicope" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Sapindales" pageId="3" pageNumber="80" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="balgooyi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="80">Melicope balgooyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was discovered around the tall spire-like peak of Pokumaru (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. A Habit of Melicope balgooyi Appelhans, W. L. Wagner &amp; K. R. Wood in situ B Habitat of Melicope balgooyi around the steep precipitous slopes of Pokumaru, Rapa, Austral Islands." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/10699" pageId="3" pageNumber="80">Fig. 4b</figureCitation>
) between 550 and 580 m. The habitat is characterized by a windswept shrubland and forest that runs along and below an east to west ridgeline. The plant communities around Pokumaru are unique with small relictual patches of tropical montane cloud forest (TMCF) along with adjacent wet cliffs and steep slopes dominated by 
<taxonomicName class="Monocotyledoneae" family="Pandanaceae" genus="Freycinetia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Pandanales" pageId="3" pageNumber="80" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="arborea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="80">Freycinetia arborea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Gaudich. Tree species in the TMCF zone which are associated with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Appelhans, W. L. Wagner &amp; K. R. Wood" authorityYear="2014" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rutaceae" genus="Melicope" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Sapindales" pageId="3" pageNumber="80" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="balgooyi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="80">Melicope balgooyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
include 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Fitchia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="80" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rapense">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="80">Fitchia rapense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
F. Br., 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Harms" authorityYear="1938" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Araliaceae" genus="Meryta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Apiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="80" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="choristantha">
