<taxonomicName authorityName="Appelhans, W. L. Wagner &amp; K. R. Wood" authorityYear="2014" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rutaceae" genus="Melicope" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Sapindales" pageId="3" pageNumber="80" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="balgooyi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="80">Melicope balgooyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
around the steep precipitous slopes of Pokumaru, Rapa, Austral Islands.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="81" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="81">
<pageBreakToken pageId="4" pageNumber="81" start="start">Etymology</pageBreakToken>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="81">
The species is named in honor of Dr. Max M.J. van Balgooy, a specialist of the SE Asian flora. Dr. van Balgooy has annotated the herbarium sheets of this new species stating that it is an &quot;unusual 
<taxonomicName genus="Rutaceae" lsidName="" pageId="4" pageNumber="81" rank="genus">Rutaceae</taxonomicName>
near 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rutaceae" genus="Platydesma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Sapindales" pageId="4" pageNumber="81" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="81">Platydesma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot;. Phylogenetic studies (
<bibRefCitation author="Harbaugh, DT" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Biogeography" pageId="7" pageNumber="84" pagination="230 - 241" publicationUrl="10.1111/j.1365-2699.2008.02008.x" refId="B5" refString="Harbaugh, DT, Wagner, WL, Allan, GJ, Zimmer, EA, 2009. The Hawaiian Archipelago is a stepping stone for dispersal in the Pacific: an example from the plant genus Melicope (Rutaceae). Journal of Biogeography 36 (2): 230 - 241, DOI: 10.1111/j.1365-2699.2008.02008.x" title="The Hawaiian Archipelago is a stepping stone for dispersal in the Pacific: an example from the plant genus Melicope (Rutaceae)." url="10.1111/j.1365-2699.2008.02008.x" volume="36" year="2009">Harbaugh et al. 2009</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Appelhans, MS" journalOrPublisher="Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution" pageId="7" pageNumber="84" pagination="54 - 68" publicationUrl="10.1016/j.ympev.2014.06.014" refId="B1" refString="Appelhans, MS, Wen, J, Wagner, WL, 2014a. A molecular phylogeny of Acronychia, Euodia, Melicope and relatives (Rutaceae) reveals polyphyletic genera and key innovations for species richness. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution 79: 54 - 68, DOI: 10.1016/j.ympev.2014.06.014" title="A molecular phylogeny of Acronychia, Euodia, Melicope and relatives (Rutaceae) reveals polyphyletic genera and key innovations for species richness." url="10.1016/j.ympev.2014.06.014" volume="79" year="2014 a">Appelhans et al. 2014a</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Appelhans, MS" journalOrPublisher="Botanical Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="7" pageNumber="84" pagination="425 - 448" publicationUrl="10.1111/boj.12123" refId="B2" refString="Appelhans, MS, Wen, J, Wood, KR, Allan, GJ, Zimmer, EA, Wagner, WL, 2014b. Molecular phylogenetic analysis of Hawaiian Rutaceae (Melicope, Platydesma and Zanthoxylum) and their different colonisation patterns. Botanical Journal of the Linnean Society 174: 425 - 448, DOI: 10.1111/boj.12123" title="Molecular phylogenetic analysis of Hawaiian Rutaceae (Melicope, Platydesma and Zanthoxylum) and their different colonisation patterns." url="10.1111/boj.12123" volume="174" year="2014 b">2014b</bibRefCitation>
) have shown that 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rutaceae" genus="Platydesma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Sapindales" pageId="4" pageNumber="81" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="81">Platydesma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is included within 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rutaceae" genus="Melicope" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Sapindales" pageId="4" pageNumber="81" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="81">Melicope</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, proving Dr. van 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Balgooy’s">Balgooy's</normalizedToken>
assumptions to be true. In addition to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="T. G. Hartley" authorityYear="2001" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rutaceae" genus="Melicope" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Sapindales" pageId="4" pageNumber="81" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="maxii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="81">Melicope maxii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
T.G. Hartley, which is endemic to Sulawesi (Indonesia), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Appelhans, W. L. Wagner &amp; K. R. Wood" authorityYear="2014" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rutaceae" genus="Melicope" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Sapindales" pageId="4" pageNumber="81" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="balgooyi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="81">Melicope balgooyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the second species of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rutaceae" genus="Melicope" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Sapindales" pageId="4" pageNumber="81" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="81">Melicope</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
named after Dr. van Balgooy.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
